<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="17">
The species 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Thiaridae" genus="Melanoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="[unassigned] Caenogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pyramis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Melanoides pyramis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="T.Hutton" baseAuthorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Thiaridae" genus="Melanoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="[unassigned] Caenogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Melanoides tigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which have been mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Annandale, N" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="18 - 62" refId="B3" refString="Annandale, N, Prashad, B, 1919. The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan. Records of the Indian Museum 18: 18 - 62" title="The Mollusca Fauna of the Inland Waters of Baluchistan and of Seistan." volume="18" year="1919">Annandale and Prashad (1911)</bibRefCitation>
from Seistan and Baluchistan, have been listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Westerlund, CA" journalOrPublisher="Turkish Journal of Zoology" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B60" refString="Westerlund, CA, 1886. Fauna der in der palaearctischen Region lebenden Binnenconchylien. 6:Fam. Ampullaridae, Paludinidae, Rissoidae, Assiminidae, Valvatidae, Melanidae &amp; Neritidae. Lund (Ohlsson), 156+13 pp." title="Fauna der in der palaearctischen Region lebenden Binnenconchylien. 6: Fam. Ampullaridae, Paludinidae, Rissoidae, Assiminidae, Valvatidae, Melanidae &amp; Neritidae. Lund (Ohlsson), 156 + 13 pp." year="1886">Westerlund (1886)</bibRefCitation>
as subspecies. However, due to the high morphological plasticity of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. F. Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Thiaridae" genus="Melanoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="[unassigned] Caenogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Melanoides tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in absence of any geographical seperation of these taxa, we list all 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Thiaridae" genus="Melanoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="[unassigned] Caenogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Melanoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. F. Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" class="Gastropoda" family="Thiaridae" genus="Melanoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="[unassigned] Caenogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="17" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="17">Melanoides tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
